      "content": "An electrical glitch causing a constant humming noise in your AC unit is less common, but it's possible there could be an issue with the relay or control board. These components are responsible for activating the motor and fan when the system is on. If these are malfunctioning due to age, dirt, or electrical problems, they might emit a humming sound without starting the fan. Before you attempt to inspect these components, ensure the power is off and that you understand the layout of your AC unit. If you're not comfortable with electrical components, it's best to consult with a professional. Remember, working with AC units can be dangerous due to high voltage, so it's essential to prioritize safety.",
